.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-7-2::.
4 different games are played: scrabble, snooker, backgammon, whist
There 4 different types of food: blueberry, cauliflower, pepper, raspberry
The people use 4 different means of transport: taxi, tram, train, boat
 1. the person eating raspberry is on the far left or far right##3
 2. the person eating blueberry is in an odd position##4
 3. the person playing backgammon is not the person eating cauliflower##6
 4. the person playing whist is the person eating pepper##1
 5. the person eating blueberry is the person driving the train##1
 6. the person eating pepper is the person driving the boat##1
 7. the person playing backgammon is on the right of the person driving the tram##1
 8. the person eating raspberry is on the left or right of the person driving the tram##3
 9. the person playing scrabble is somewhere between the person eating raspberry and the person playing backgammon##7
10. the person driving the train is on the left or right of the person eating pepper##3

.:: Answer ::.
|               |       1       |      2      |     3     |   4    |
| Game      | snooker | scrabble         | backgammon    | whist  |
| Food          | raspberry     | cauliflower | blueberry | pepper |
| Transport   | taxi     | tram     | train  | boat |

